AGI - A year after the disappearance will be issued a stamp dedicated to Silvio Berlusconi. The news was given today at the end of the Council of Ministers which approved the new 2024 philosophic plan. The presidential decree authorizing the issue of commemorative and celebratory postal values was elaborated, on the basis of the proposals received, by the Administration who also acquired the opinion of the Consulta. In particular, we read in a note, appropriate stamps will remember Marsilio Ficino, Guglielmo Marconi, on the 150th anniversary of birth; St. Thomas Aquinas, on the 750th anniversary of the disappearance; Giacomo Puccini, Giacomo Matteotti and Eleonora Duse in the centenary of the disappearance; Giovanni Gentile, on the 80th anniversary of his death. It will also be remembered Libero Grassi, Franco Basaglia, Alberto Manzi, Carlo Melograni, in the centenary of birth; Giuseppe Tatarella, on the 25th anniversary of the disappearance; Silvio Berlusconi a year after his death. In the previous edition, commemorative stamps were made for David Sassoli and Franco Frattini.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
<h2> The plause of Forza Italia</h2>
"The stamp dedicated to President Silvio Berlusconi, who will be issued a year after his death, is the right recognition to a great Italian who served and honored the Republic in all the roles he held: Entrepreneur, man of sport, political leader and statesman." To announce it are the vice president FI of the Senate, Licia Ronzulli, and the deputy 'azzurro' Paolo Emilio Russo, in thanking "the president Meloni and the whole Council of Ministers to have accepted the proposal of the minister of the Enterprises and the Made in Italy, Adolfo Urso, and the undersecretary delegated Fausta Bergamotto".
