AGI&nbsp;- If Democratic Party and Movement 5 Stars could update the sentimental status of their social profiles they would choose: "In a complicated relationship." Difficult dialogue and even more difficult the relationship, with the European elections at the doors and that proportional electoral law with preferences that does not lead anyone to invest in alliances and coalitions. Indeed, if there is a moment when political forces can weigh and weigh (especially with allies) their consent is precisely that of European consultations. If the investigations of Bari and Turin are added to this, which involved local managers in different ways, the company becomes at the limits of the impossible.
&nbsp;
Because the 5 Star Movement has made its "polar star" legality, to say it with President Giuseppe Conte, who, after having 'injected the rospo' of the primaries of coalition in Bari, blown the table when Michele Emiliano has elongated the shadow of the sale of votes. To this is added the Piedmontese inquiry that involves the father of the group leader Pd in the region, Raffaele Gallo, immediately resigned from the assignment. From here the appeal addressed by the former premier to Elly Schlein because&nbsp; "change the Pd before the Pd changes her".
&nbsp;
A tense leg surgery that is badly digested in the house Pd, especially from that party piece that has always seen as smoke in the eyes the axis with the Five Stars. "Contin's Law that inspires Elly Schlein to transform the Pd, worth letting itself be transformed by the old Pd, makes me really angry. How dare you?", asks the mayor of Bergamo, Giorgio Gori: "The Pd is made by thousands of women and men for good. A party with a minimum of spine should not allow anyone to talk like that."
&nbsp;
But even from the national secretariat Pd arrive precise signals to the leader M5s: "Before teaching morality on the right and left, Count evaluated whether the opportunism of doing and undoing political agreements for electoral calculation is ethically recommended," says Justice Debora Serracchiani. "With the M5S militants we are keeping open constructive dialogues on many territories and there is mutual respect, but we do not feel any need for anyone outside our party to come and give us the line and dictate conditions," he adds. The secretary Schlein remains far from the controversy, although the words spoken in Bari still resonate: "So you help the right." The Pd is still in support of the candidate Vito Leccese as well as the M5s is on Michele Laforgia. An iron arm behind which the 'pontieri' move, both at national level - it is seen with the call of Goffredo Bettini and Andrea Orlando to turn on a third shared name - both locally, as indicated by the words of Schlein. "We will support Vito" Leccese "although it will still attempt dialogue to find a unitary solution, but without accepting any imposition".
&nbsp;
And Leccese assured that he wanted to continue the search for a unitary solution which, however, required the agreement of both candidates. Michele Laforgia does not close, reasserting that a withdrawal of both nominations for a third name is difficult. Hypothesis also rejected by Count: "It's not in the order of things." While comparing with the reluctant ally, Schlein continues to work on applications for European lists, leaving Igor Taruffi, head of the Organization, the task of developing the self-regulation code that in the Pd already call "anti-cacicchi code".
&nbsp;
The instrument, explained by parliamentary sources, could recalculate that launched today by Commissioner Pd in Campania, Antonio Misiani in which, among other things, it is expected that the candidates for the administration sign a written commitment to denounce any attempt to vote of exchange, corruption, concussion, intimidation that should occur during the electoral campaign. Along with this, "the commitment to inspire political and administrative action to the principles of transparency, legality, tension to the common good and to develop forms of active participation of citizens and citizens". A regulation that seems to be written in the light of what has been seen in Bari and Piedmont, although &nbsp; the work, Misiani explains, " began three months ago, recovering and developing a series of good practices of transparency adopted in the past in some administrative elections in Campania".
&nbsp;
A track to work on for the future. Also because, among other interventions, at national level could find more stringent rules on some issues, such as the number of mandates. If it is true, in fact, that the Code of Ethics of the PD is in force since the birth of the party and that it has been made more stringent over time, it is also true that the frequent use of "deroms" has allowed to bypass some stakes like that, precisely, of the mandates. The dossier, which is "in total availability" of the secretary dem, to say it with a parliamentary source Pd, is instead that of the lists for Europeans. Time tightens and expects the call of the direction, moment truth for the aspiring candidates Pd. The main nodes concern the positioning of the leader dem and that of the civic representatives, from Lucia Annunziata to marco Tarquinio passing through Cecilia Strada and Pietro Bartolo. Also waited for the big who contend to the ombuds the pole position: Stefano Bonaccini in the North East, Andrea Orlando in the North West, Dario Nardella and Nicola Zingaretti at the Centre, Antonio Decaro in the South. A sudoku for skilled solutors who have produced fibrillations in the past to bring the Pd near the split (as happened to Renzi in 2018). &nbsp;

